{"word":"ἐνέπω","slug":"ἐνέπω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐνέπω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>a <a href='S:lengthened'>lengthd.</a> form of *<el>ἔπω, εἰπεῖν</el>,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to tell, tell of, relate, describe</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to tell news</i> or <i>tales</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>simply <i>to speak</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to bid</i> one <i>do</i> so and so, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>to call</i> so and so, <el>ἐνν. τινὰ δοῦλον</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>5. </b>= <a href='S:προσεννέπω'><el>προσεννέπω</el></a>, <i>to address</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}